{"word":"Δήλιος","slug":"Δήλιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>Δήλιος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Δῆλος'><el>Δῆλος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>Delian</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<el>ὁ Δ.</el>, name of Apollo, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a Delian</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><el>τὰ Δήλια</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> <el>ἱερά</el>) <i>the quinquennial festival of Apollo at Delos</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}